We loved our stay at this property and the food was delicious. We loved the lush green ambience, quiet from the hustle bustle of the city. 

The USP of our cozy cottage stay was it’s open air Washroom! We loved it! Perfect for couples looking to spend quality time

If you go after February you can access their vineyards and even taste the fresh grapes from the vines itself..

latestPosts.caption:
10 hacks to save big when you’re about to land in Switzerland:

💡 1. Get a Swiss Travel Pass ( We opted for half fare card i.e 50% off on every public transport) 

Unlimited rides on trains, buses, boats, and discounts on mountain excursions.

⸻

🛒 2. Shop at Supermarkets
	•	Eat cheap from Coop, Migros, or Aldi.
	•	Grab picnic items or pre-made meals instead of dining out.

⸻

💧 3. Refill Your Water Bottle
	•	Tap water is clean, cold, and free — even from fountains!

⸻

🏨 4. Stay in Hostels or Airbnb
	•	Hostels in Switzerland are clean, safe, and often include breakfast.
	•	Airbnb apartments help you cook your own meals.

⸻

🏔️ 5. Choose Free Natural Attractions
	•	Hike, explore lakes, waterfalls, and mountains for zero cost.

⸻

🚂6. Download SBB app for train timings

⸻

🚶‍♂️ 7. Walk or Rent a Bike
	•	Swiss cities are walkable and often offer free public bikes.

⸻

🕰️ 8. Visit Museums on Free Days
	•	Many museums have free entry days or are included with the Swiss Pass.

⸻

💳 9. Use a Travel Card or Wise App
	•	Avoid high foreign transaction fees and bad exchange rates.

⸻

⛺ 10. Camp or Stay in Alpine Huts
	•	Budget-friendly and scenic alternatives to hotels in mountain regions.

latestPosts.caption:
📍P O S I T A N O

Here’s a 3-day Positano itinerary that balances iconic sights, food, relaxation, and a little adventure.

Day 1: Explore Positano Town & Beaches

Morning:
	•	Arrive in Positano and check into your accommodation.
	•	Grab a cappuccino and pastry at La Zagara or Casa e Bottega.
	•	Walk around the winding streets, browse local boutiques and ceramic shops.

Afternoon:
	•	Relax at Spiaggia Grande (main beach).
	•	Lunch at Chez Black or Ristorante La Pergola—right by the beach.

Evening:
	•	Sunset drinks at Franco’s Bar (amazing views).
	•	Dinner at Ristorante La Sponda (Michelin-starred, romantic setting at Le Sirenuse Hotel).

⸻

Day 2: Amalfi Coast Adventure

Morning:
	•	Take a boat trip or ferry to Amalfi and Ravello (book a private tour or hop-on/hop-off ferry).
	•	Explore Amalfi Cathedral and enjoy limoncello tasting.

Afternoon:
	•	Head to Ravello, visit Villa Rufolo and Villa Cimbrone.
	•	Lunch at Ristorante Vittoria (Ravello) or picnic with views.

Evening:
	•	Return to Positano.
	•	Dinner at Next2 or Il Capitano (beautiful sea views).

⸻

Day 3: Hike & Hidden Spots

Morning:
	•	Early morning hike on the Path of the Gods (Sentiero degli Dei) from Nocelle.
	•	Enjoy breathtaking views over the coast.

Afternoon:
	•	Lunch in Nocelle at La Tagliata (farm-to-table, epic views).
	•	Take a break at Fornillo Beach (quieter than Spiaggia Grande).

Evening:
	•	Aperitivo on a terrace—try Villa Franca’s rooftop bar.
	•	Farewell dinner at Zass (Il San Pietro di Positano) if you want a luxurious splurge.

⸻

Tips:
	•	Wear comfy shoes—lots of stairs!
	•	Book boat tours and restaurants in advance during peak season (May–Sept).
	•	Use ferries or private transfers to avoid narrow, congested roads.

latestPosts.caption:
📍Amalfi Coast Itinerary from Sorrento (We reached Sorrento from Naples)

Day 1: Positano & Amalfi

Morning: Positano

⚡️Take an early ferry or bus to Positano (about 30–40 mins).
⚡️Wander through the narrow streets, shop for linen clothes & handmade sandals.
Visit Church of Santa Maria Assunta.
⚡️Chill at Spiaggia Grande or grab a lemon granita with that iconic view.

Lunch: Dine at La Pergola or Chez Black on the beach.

Afternoon: Amalfi
⚡️Ferry to Amalfi (~25 mins).
⚡️Explore Amalfi Cathedral & the Cloister of Paradise.
⚡️Taste the legendary Amalfi lemon sorbet.
⚡️Optional hike to Valle delle Ferriere if you love nature & waterfalls.

Evening: Return to Sorrento
⚡️Enjoy sunset views on the ferry back.
⚡️Dinner in Sorrento: try Ristorante L’Antica Trattoria for authentic Campanian cuisine.

⸻

Day 2: Ravello & Atrani

Morning: Ravello
⚡️Take a bus or private transfer up to Ravello (from Amalfi, ~20 mins uphill).
⚡️Visit Villa Rufolo and Villa Cimbrone—their gardens & cliff views are unreal.
⚡️Stroll through the peaceful piazzas.

Lunch: Eat at Villa Maria with panoramic terrace views.

Afternoon: Atrani
⚡️Walk down (or take a short ride) to Atrani, Amalfi’s quieter sister village.
⚡️Explore its small piazza and swim at the beach if weather permits.

Evening: Return to Sorrento
⚡️Catch a ferry or bus back.
⚡️Dinner: Porta Marina Seafood (by the Marina Grande) for fresh seafood and sea views.

⸻

Day 3: Day trip to Capri. But We opted to come back to Naples as we had a flight back to Paris! 
.
